description: Experimental values for maximal number of "loose" circles in packing equal circles into a square.
references: H. T. Croft, K. J. Falconer and R. K. Guy: Unsolved problems in geometry, Springer, New York, 1991.
links: D. Boll, Optimal Packing Of Circles And Spheres
C. D. Maranas, C. A. Floudas and P.M. Pardalos, New results in the packing of equal circles in a square, Discrete Mathematics 142 (1995), p. 287-293.
K. J. Nurmela and P. R. J. Ostergard, Packing up to 50 equal circles in a square, Discrete Comput. Geom. 18 (1997) 1, p. 111-120.
author: Eckard Specht (eckard.specht(AT)physik.uni-magdeburg.de)
extensions: I do not know how many of these values have been rigorously proved - _N. J. A. Sloane_.
